English Language

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

Over the past month, our General English class has been buzzing with activity and progress! We've been diving into exciting lessons that focus on real-world language use, enhancing our speaking, listening, and writing skills. The highlight of the month was our memorable excursion to the Royal Academy of Arts, Fortnum and Mason, and the Leicester Square Christmas Market, where we explored art, enjoyed festive treats, and embraced the holiday spirit. We’ve also been thrilled to welcome new students to our class, who have already become a wonderful part of our vibrant learning community. It’s been a month full of learning, laughter, and new experiences!

London Art Exhibits and Christmas Market

 

 

London Art Exhibits and Christmas Market

 

 

 

Our General English class went on an unforgettable excursion to some of London's most iconic spots! We explored the stunning art exhibits at the Royal Academy of Arts, indulged in festive delights at Fortnum and Mason, and soaked in the holiday magic at the Leicester Square Christmas Market! A perfect blend of culture, shopping, and Christmas cheer!

British Library

 

 

British Library

 

Chinese New Year

 

 

Chinese New Year

 

 

 

Looking for a place where history, culture, and knowledge come together? Visit the British Library! As one of the largest and most prestigious libraries in the world, it offers an incredible collection of books, manuscripts, and artifacts, including original works by Shakespeare, Magna Carta, and much more. Whether you're a history buff, a book lover, or simply looking for a quiet spot to study, the British Library is a must-see destination. With free exhibitions, a café, and stunning architecture, it’s the perfect place to explore and inspire your curiosity. Don't miss out—plan your visit today!

Celebrate Chinese New Year in the heart of London! Immerse yourself in the vibrant culture and traditions of this exciting festival with spectacular parades, mesmerizing dragon dances, and a feast of delicious street food. Whether you're exploring Chinatown or joining the lively festivities across the city, there's something for everyone to enjoy. Experience the colorful decorations, lively performances, and shop for unique gifts and crafts that bring good luck and prosperity. Don't miss out on London's grand celebration of the Year of the Snake – a memorable experience awaits you!

Sport of the Month

Hidden London Walking Tour

 

 

 

Sport of the Month

Hidden London Walking Tour

 

 

 

 

Get ready to be spellbound by the sensational musical Wicked! Join Elphaba and Glinda in this critically acclaimed production that tells the untold story of the witches of Oz. With breathtaking choreography, spectacular sets, and a powerful score that includes hits like "Defying Gravity," Wicked is a theatrical experience you won’t want to miss. Whether you're seeing it for the first time or returning for another round of magic, this unforgettable show will leave you mesmerized. Book your tickets now and prepare for a night of enchantment, humor, and heart!

Discover the secret side of London with Hidden London Walking Tours! Step off the beaten path and explore the city's forgotten history, hidden gems, and untold stories with our expert guides. From hidden courtyards to abandoned stations and overlooked landmarks, each tour offers a fascinating glimpse into the capital's mysterious past. Whether you're a lifelong Londoner or a curious visitor, our tours promise a unique adventure through the hidden corners of this iconic city. Book your tour today and uncover the hidden treasures of London!
